This paper deals with information leakage and its measurement, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the effect of side information on this measure, which is related to the field of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper uses mathematical optimization techniques to derive its results, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the concept of channel capacity, which is a fundamental concept in communication theory (cs.CC).
